# InverBrass Approved Platform Stack

Use only the approved technologies unless explicitly instructed otherwise.

---

# Frontend

Framework:
- Next.js 15+ (App Router)

Language:
- TypeScript

UI Framework:
- React 19

Styling:
- Tailwind CSS

UI Components:
- shadcn/ui

Icons:
- Lucide React

Forms:
- React Hook Form
- Zod validation

State Management:
- React Context for shared application state.
- Server State through Next.js Server Components.
- Avoid introducing Redux, MobX or other state libraries unless explicitly approved.

Mobile Strategy:
- Progressive Web App (PWA)
- Mobile-first responsive design

---

# Backend

Application Architecture:
- Next.js Route Handlers
- Next.js Server Actions
- Modular Monolith architecture

API Style:
- REST APIs
- JSON payloads

Validation:
- Zod

Authentication:
- Supabase Auth

Authorization:
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

File Storage:
- Supabase Storage

Background Processing:
- Trigger only when approved.
- Prefer lightweight scheduled jobs over unnecessary background services.

---

# Database

# Database Platform
Approved Database Engine:
- PostgreSQL
Current Managed Platform:
- Supabase
The application shall be designed so that PostgreSQL can be hosted on:
- Supabase
- Self-managed PostgreSQL
- Azure Database for PostgreSQL
- AWS RDS PostgreSQL
- Google Cloud SQL
- Any standards-compliant PostgreSQL deployment
ORM:

- Drizzle ORM

Migration Tool:

- Drizzle Kit


Database Access Principles:
- Parameterized queries only.
- Never use raw SQL unless absolutely necessary.
- Preserve referential integrity.
- Design for multi-tenancy.

---

# Testing

Unit Testing:
- Vitest

Integration Testing:
- Vitest

End-to-End Testing:
- Playwright

Linting:
- ESLint

Formatting:
- Prettier

---

# Logging & Monitoring

Application Logging:
- Pino

Error Handling:
- Structured error responses.
- Never expose internal implementation details.

Monitoring:
- Build with observability in mind.
- Design code to support future monitoring and diagnostics.

---

# Integrations

Primary Integrations:

- Safaricom Daraja API
- WhatsApp Business API
- Email (SMTP/API)
- SMS Gateway
- REST APIs
- Webhooks

Build integrations through reusable service layers.

---

# AI

Primary AI Assistant:
- ChatGPT (Architecture, Design Review, Code Review)

Primary Development Assistant:
- Cursor AI

AI Principles:
- AI assists development.
- AI does not replace engineering judgement.
- Architectural decisions require human approval.

---

# Project Structure

Follow the approved repository structure.

Do not create alternative project structures.

Respect module boundaries.

Keep shared code inside approved shared libraries.

Do not duplicate platform capabilities.

---

# Package Management

Package Manager:
- npm

Only introduce new dependencies when:

- They provide clear business value.
- They are actively maintained.
- They are compatible with the approved stack.
- Existing platform capabilities cannot solve the problem.

Always explain why a new dependency is required before recommending it.

---

# Prohibited Technologies

Unless explicitly approved, do NOT introduce:

- Angular
- Vue
- Svelte
- Express.js
- NestJS
- Prisma ORM
- MongoDB
- MySQL
- Firebase
- Redux
- MobX
- Bootstrap
- Material UI
- jQuery

Do not replace approved technologies with personal preferences.

---

# Engineering Philosophy

Prefer:

- Simplicity
- Consistency
- Reusability
- Maintainability
- Enterprise scalability

Avoid:

- Framework proliferation.
- Duplicate libraries.
- Experimental technologies in production.
- Over-engineering.
- Vendor lock-in where practical alternatives exist.

The approved platform stack is the foundation of the InverBrass Platform and shall remain consistent across all Build Packs unless formally changed.
